{
  "text": "[4] Two independent studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] -using distinct coupled modelshave compared model integrations with high and low stratospheric ozone and found a robust, if perhaps unexpected, result: that ozone depletion, over a period of several decades, causes Antarctic SIE to markedly decrease. This was further confirmed, in the context of ozone recovery, by a third study using a stratosphere-resolving model with interactively coupled stratospheric chemistry [CITATION_3] .",
